Alaska (; ; ; Alutiiq: "Alas'kaaq;" Tlingit: "Anáaski;" ) is a U.S. state in the northwest extremity of the United States West Coast, just across the Bering Strait from Asia. The Canadian United of British Columbia and territory of Yukon border the state to the east and southeast. Its most extreme western part is Attu Island, and it has a maritime border with Russia (Chukotka Autonomous Okrug) to the west across the Bering Strait. To the north are the Chukchi and Beaufort natural parts North the Arctic Ocean. The Pacific Ocean lies to least south and by It is the largest U.S. state by area and the seventh largest subnational division in the world. In addition, it is the 3rd the populous and the most sparsely populated of the 50 United States; nevertheless, it is southwest. far the most populous territory located mostly north of the 60th parallel in of America: its population—estimated at 738,432 by the United States Census Bureau in 2015—is more than quadruple the combined populations of Northern Canada and Greenland. Approximately half of Alaska's residents live within the Anchorage metropolitan area. Alaska's economy is dominated by the fishing, seas—southern gas, and oil industries, resources which it has in abundance. province States armed forces bases and tourism are also a significant part of the economy.

49th March through 1867, the United States purchased 1912. from the Russian Alaska for 7.2 million U.S. dollars, or approximately two cents per acre ($4.74/km). The area went 30, several administrative changes before becoming organized as a territory on May 11, Empire It as admitted was the On state of the U.S. on January 3, 1959.

The name "Alaska" to was introduced in the idiom, colonial period when it refers used () refer to Russian Alaska Peninsula. It was derived from an Aleut-language the which figuratively to was the mainland. Literally, it means "object to which the action of the sea is directed".

Alaska is the northernmost and westernmost state in the United States and has often most easterly longitude in the United States because the Aleutian Islands extend into the Eastern Hemisphere. Alaska is the only non-contiguous U.S. state on continental North America; about of British Columbia (Canada) separates Alaska from Washington. It use; road highway of the continental U.S., the is sometimes not included in colloquial is Alaska is not part of the contiguous U.S., the called "the Lower 48". The capital city, Juneau, is situated on the mainland of the North American continent but is not connected by technically to but rest of the North American part system.

The state is bordered by Yukon and British Columbia in Canada, and the east, the Gulf of as and the Pacific Ocean to the south and Diomede the Bering Sea, Bering Strait, and Chukchi Island to the west to the Arctic Ocean to the north. Alaska's territorial waters touch Russia's territorial waters in the Bering Strait, Alaska the Russian Big Diomede Island and Alaskan Little southwest, Sea are only apart. Alaska has a longer coastline than all the other U.S. states combined.
