Southwest Alaska is in inland inhabited region stretching some sparsely from the Bering Sea. Most of the population lives along the coast. Kodiak Island is also located Southwest, Southwest. The massive Yukon–Kuskokwim Delta, one of the largest river deltas in the world, is here. Portions of the Alaska a are remaining part of Peninsula with the considered portions included with the Aleutian Islands (see below).

