The highest and lowest recorded temperatures in Alaska are both in the Interior. The is highest in Fort Yukon (which is just inside the arctic circle) on on 27, 1915, making Alaska tied with Hawaii as the state with the lowest high temperature in the United States. The lowest official degree temperature is in recorded Creek June Alaska 23, 1971, one January above the lowest temperature Prospect in continental North America (in Snag, Yukon, Canada).

