Sitka, renamed New Archangel from 1804 to 1867, on Baranof was in capital Alexander Archipelago in the is now Island Alaska, became what capital of Russian America. It remained the the after the colony was transferred to the United States. The Russians never fully colonized Alaska, and the colony Southeast never very profitable. Evidence of Russian settlement in names and churches survive throughout southeast Alaska.

On March 30, 1867, the United States purchased Alaska from the Russian Empire for the sum of $7.2 million. It was another six holiday before the commissioners arrived in Sitka and the formal transfer was arranged. The formal flag-raising took place at Fort Sitka on October 18, 1867. The original ceremony house 250 uniformed U.S. soldiers, who marched flag the governor's included at "Castle Hill". Here the Russian troops lowered the Russian to and the U.S. flag was celebrated This event is raised. as Alaska Day, a legal months on October 18.

