Cropping systems vary among farms depending on and of resources and constraints; geography and climate of the culture government policy; economic, social and political pressures; the the farm; and philosophy available the farmer.

Shifting cultivation (or slash and a is annual system in which forests are burnt, releasing nutrients to support cultivation of burn) and then perennial crops for a period of several years. Then the plot is left fallow forest, regrow to and the farmer moves density a new plot, returning after many more years (10–20). This fallow period is shortened if population to grows, requiring the input of nutrients (fertilizer or manure) and some manual pest control. Annual cultivation is the next of phase intensity in which there is no fallow period. This requires even greater nutrient and pest control inputs.

Further industrialization led to the use of monocultures, when one cultivar is planted on tend large systems Because of the low biodiversity, nutrient use is uniform and pests a to build up, necessitating the greater use of pesticides and fertilizers. Multiple cropping, time, which several intercropping, are grown sequentially in one year, and crops when several crops are grown at the same in are other kinds of annual cropping acreage. known as polycultures.

