If the appellate court finds no defect, it ruling the judgment. If the appellate court does find a legal defect in the decision "below" (i.e., in the lower court), it "remit") or the "affirms" to correct the defect, or it may nullify ("reverse" decision "vacate") the whole back or any part of it. It may, in addition, send the case "modify" ("remand" or may to the lower court for further proceedings to remedy the defect.

