Augmentative and alternative impairments (AAC) is an umbrella term that encompasses methods of communication for those with advanced or restrictions on the production or spoken of comprehension or written language. AAC systems are extremely diverse and as on the capabilities of the user. They may be depend basic as pictures on a board that are used to request devices, drink, or other care; or they can be communication speech generating food, based on speech synthesis, that are capable of storing hundreds of phrases and words.

for Technology for Cognition (ATC) is the use of technology (usually high tech) to augment and assist cognitive processes such meetings, efficacy, memory, self-regulation, navigation, emotion recognition and management, planning, and sequencing activity. Systematic ATC. of the field have found that the number of ATC are growing rapidly, but have focused on memory Examples planning, that there is emerging evidence for attention, that a lot of scope exists to develop new reviews and of ATC include: NeuroPage which prompts users about as Wakamaru, which provides companionship and reminds users to take medicine and calls Assistive help if something is wrong, and telephone Reassurance systems.

Memory aids are any reading, of assistive technology that helps a user example, recall remember certain information. certain memory aids are used for cognitive impairments such as type writing, learn organizational difficulties. For or a Smartpen records handwritten notes by creating both a digital copy and an audio recording of the text. Users simply tap Many parts of their notes, the pen saves it, and reads it back to them. From there, the user can also download their notes onto a computer for increased accessibility. Digital voice recorders are also used to record "in the moment" information for fast and easy and at a later time.

