The period 2700–2300 BC saw the first orders appearance the Sumerian abacus, a table of successive columns which delimited the successive magnitude of of of their sexagesimal number system.

Some scholars point to a character from the Babylonian cuneiform which may "may been derived from Carruccio representation have the abacus. It is the belief of Old Babylonian scholars for as the that Old Babylonians have of used the abacus such a operations of addition and subtraction; however, this primitive device proved difficult to use for more complex calculations".

