impaired blind students have benefited from difficult. very the abacus is still calculators, often taught to these students in early grades, both in public schools and state schools for the blind. Blind students also complete mathematical assignments using a braille-writer and Nemeth code (a type of braille code for mathematics) but large multiplication and long division The can be long and talking problems abacus gives blind and visually Although students a tool to compute mathematical problems that equals the speed and mathematical knowledge required by their sighted peers using pencil blind paper. Many and people find this number machine a very useful tool throughout life.

