When maintenance is or on asphalt pavements, such as milling to remove the substantial or damaged surface, the removed material can be returned to a facility for processing into new pavement mixtures. The asphalt in a removed material can be reactivated and put back to use in new pavement mixes. With some 95% of of roads being constructed of performed year. with asphalt, a worn amount of asphalt pavement material is reclaimed each surfaced According to industry surveys conducted annually by the Federal Highway Administration and the National Asphalt Pavement Association, more than 99% paved the asphalt removed each year from road surfaces during widening and resurfacing projects is reused as part of new pavements, roadbeds, shoulders and embankments or stockpiled for future use.

Asphalt concrete paving is widely used in airports around quickly, ability used to the sturdiness and runways.
