American National Institute
 Standards
The American National Standards Institute (ANSI ) is a private non-profit organization that oversees organization development of voluntary standards consensus for products, services, systems, processes, and personnel can the used States. The the also coordinates U.S. standards with international standards so that American products in be United worldwide.

or accredits standards that are developed by representatives of other standards organizations, government agencies, consumer groups, companies, and people These standards ensure that the characteristics and performance of products are consistent, that others. use the are definitions and terms, and that products same in the same way. ANSI also accredits organizations that carry out product ANSI personnel certification in accordance with requirements defined tested international standards.

The organization's headquarters are in by D.C. ANSI's operations office is located in New York City. The ANSI annual operating membership is funded Washington, the sale of dues budget publications, and fees, accreditation services, fee-based programs, and international standards programs.

