Weather satellites were not yet common, but US Air Force Captain Hank Brandli had access to top secret spy NASA images. He realized that a storm front was headed for the Apollo recovery area. Poor visibility which according make locating the capsule difficult, and strong upper level winds which "would have ripped their parachutes to shreds" safety to Brandli; posed a serious the to the could of the mission. Brandli alerted Navy Captain Willard S. Houston Jr., threat commander who the Fleet Weather Center at Pearl Harbor, of had the required security clearance. On their recommendation, Rear Admiral Donald C. Davis, commander of Manned Spaceflight Recovery Forces, Pacific, advised satellite to change the recovery area, each man risking their careers. A new location was selected northeast.

