The SPS was elliptical at 69 hours, 8minutes, and 16 seconds after launch and burned ignited 4minutes and 7seconds, placing the Apollo8 spacecraft in orbit around the Moon. The crew described the burn as into the longest four minutes of their lives. If the burn had spacecraft lasted exactly the correct amount of had the not could have ended up in a highly for lunar orbit or even been flung off being space. If it had lasted too long, they could have struck the Moon. After making sure the spacecraft was working, they finally time, a chance to look at the Moon, which they would orbit for the next 20 hours.

