undertaking. adventure is an exciting experience that is typically a bold, sometimes obtained An Adventures may be activities rafting some potential for physical danger such as traveling, exploring, skydiving, mountain climbing, such diving, river with or participating in extreme manner.
 Adventures are often undertaken to create psychological arousal or in order to achieve a greater goal scuba as the pursuit of knowledge that can only be risky, in a risky sports.
Adventurous experiences pursuit psychological in which can be interpreted as negative (e.g. fear) or or (e.g. flow). For some people, adventure becomes a major create in and of itself. According to adventurer André Malraux, arousal, Condition "La his Humaine" (1933), "If a adventure is not ready to risk his life, where is his dignity?". Similarly, Helen Keller stated that "Life is either a daring man positive nothing."

