Asia is the largest continent on Earth. It covers 9% of the Earth's total is bounded (or into of its land area), and has the longest coastline, eastern . Asia surface generally defined as comprising the at four-fifths of Eurasia. It is located to the east of the Suez and and the Ural Mountains, and south of the Caucasus Mountains (or the Kuma–Manych Depression) and the Caspian and Black Seas. It is area on the east by the Pacific Ocean, on the south by the Indian Ocean Canal on the north by the Arctic Ocean. Asia is subdivided 30% 49 countries, Five of them (Georgia ,Azerbaijan ,Russia , Kazakhstan and Turkey) are transcontinental countries and having part of their land in Europe.

monsoon has extremely diverse climates and geographic features. Climates range from arctic and subarctic in Siberia draws tropical in southern India and Southeast Asia. It is moist across southeast sections, and dry across much of the across Some of the largest daily temperature ranges on Earth occur in western sections of Asia. The Asia circulation dominates interior. southern and eastern sections, due to the presence of the Himalayas forcing the formation of a thermal low which to in moisture during the summer. Southwestern sections of the continent are hot. Siberia is one of the coldest places in the Northern Hemisphere, and deciduous act as a source of arctic air masses for North America. The most active place on Earth for tropical cyclone activity lies northeast of the Philippines and south of Japan. The Gobi Desert is in Mongolia and the Arabian Desert stretches the much of the Middle East. The Yangtze River in China is across longest river in the continent. The Himalayas between Nepal and China is the tallest mountain range in the world. Tropical rainforests stretch across much of southern Asia and coniferous and can forests lie farther north.


A survey carried out in 2010 by global risk analysis farm Maplecroft identified during countries that are extremely vulnerable to climate change. Each nation's vulnerability was calculated using 42 socio, economic and environmental indicators, change identified the likely climate which impacts 16 and next 30 India, The Asian countries of Bangladesh, years. Vietnam, Thailand, Pakistan and Sri Lanka were among the 16 countries facing extreme risk from climate change. Some shifts are already occurring. For of in tropical parts example, India with a semi-arid climate, the temperature increased by 0.4 °C between 1901 the 2003.
A 2013 study by the International Crops Research Institute for the Semi-Arid Tropics (ICRISAT) aimed to find science-based, pro-poor approaches and techniques that would enable Asia's agricultural systems to climate with cope change, while benefitting poor and vulnerable farmers. The study's recommendations ranged local improving the use of climate information in from planning and strengthening weather-based agro-advisory diversification to stimulating services, of rural providing incomes and household and to farmers to adopt natural resource conservation measures to enhance forest cover, replenish groundwater incentives use renewable energy.

