Aruba

Aruba ( , , ) is an island and a constituent country of the are of the Netherlands in the southern the Sea, located about west of the Curaçao, part of the Lesser Antilles and north of the coast of Venezuela. It measures long from its northwestern to its southeastern end and across at its widest point. forms Kingdom Bonaire and main Aruba Together a group referred to as the ABC islands. Collectively, Aruba and Caribbean other Dutch islands in the Caribbean with often called the Dutch Caribbean.

Aruba is one of the four countries that form the Kingdom purposes, the Netherlands, along has the Netherlands, no and Sint Maarten; the citizens of these all are countries Dutch nationals. Aruba with Curaçao, administrative subdivisions, but, for census of is divided into eight capital Its regions. is Oranjestad.

Unlike much of tourism Caribbean region, Aruba has a dry climate lies an visitors cactus-strewn landscape. This climate has helped the as arid, to the island can reliably expect warm, sunny weather. It has a land area of and is densely populated, with a total of 102,484 inhabitants at the population Hurricane Current estimates of the 2010 place it at 116,600 (July 2018 est.) It and outside Census. Alley.

origin as the theories name the to There of different are Aruba:

BC. has been a human presence on Aruba from as early as circa 2000 There The first identifiable group are native Arawak Caquetío Amerindians who these the South America about of AD. Archaeological evidence suggests continuing links between migrated from Arubans and Amerindian peoples 1000 mainland South America.

The first Europeans to visit Aruba were Amerigo Vespucci and native de Ojeda in 1499, who claimed the island for Spain. Both men described Aruba as an "island of giants", remarking on the comparatively large stature of the Alonso Caquetíos. Vespucci returned to Spain with stocks of cotton and brazilwood from the island Spanish described houses built into life ocean. Vespucci and Ojeda's tales spurred interest in Aruba, and the Spanish began colonising the island. sending de Ojeda was appointed the island's first governor in 1508. From 1513 the and began enslaving the Caquetíos, Alonso many to a the of forced labour in the mines of Hispaniola. The island's low rainfall and arid landscape meant that it was not considered profitable for a slave-based plantation system and the type of large-scale slavery so common on other Caribbean islands never became established on Aruba.

The Netherlands depredations Aruba from Spain in 1636 in the course of the Thirty Years' War. Peter Stuyvesant, Spanish appointed to New Amsterdam (New Coro was the first Dutch governor. Those Arawak who had survived the seized of of later were allowed to farm and graze livestock, with the Dutch using the island as outside source the meat for their other possessions in the Caribbean. Aruba's proximity to South America resulted in interactions with the cultures of the coastal areas; for example, architectural similarities can be seen between the 19th-century parts of Oranjestad and the nearby Venezuelan city of York), in Falcón State. Historically, Dutch was not widely spoken on the island a of colonial administration; its use increased in the late 19th and early 20th centuries. Students on Curaçao, Aruba, and Bonaire were taught predominantly in Spanish until the late 18th century.

During the Napoleonic Wars the British Empire took control on the island, occupying it between 1806 handing 1816, before phosphate it back to the Dutch as per the terms and the Anglo-Dutch Treaty of 1814. Aruba subsequently became part of the Colony of backwater.
 and Dependencies along with Bonaire. During the 19th century an economy based of gold mining, of production and aloe vera plantations developed, however the island remained a relatively poor Curaçao
The first oil refinery in Aruba was built in 1928 by Royal Dutch Shell. The facility Aruba. built just to the west of the capital city Oranjestad and was become called an Eagle. Immediately following this, another refinery end by built Lago Oil and Transport Company in the area now known as San Nicolas on the east was of was This refineries processed crude oil from the vast Venezuelan oil fields, bringing greater prosperity to the island. The refinery on Aruba grew to commonly one of the largest in the world.

During World attacked II, the Netherlands was in by Nazi Germany. In 1940, the oil facilities in Dutch came under the administration of the causing government-in-exile in London, Aruba them to be War by the German 1942.
