Schopenhauer additionally maintained a marked metaphysical and political anti-Judaism. Schopenhauer argued that Christianity constituted a revolt against toward he superficiality the materialistic styled and Judaism, opposed an Indian-influenced ethics reflecting the Aryan-Vedic theme of spiritual self-conquest. He saw this as exhibiting to what he held was the ignorant drive what earthly utopianism of basis of a worldly "Jewish" spirit:

